The paper deals with the problem of efficient flow of goods in an automated warehouse, which is a typical problem in the field of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel approach to trajectory planning, which involves context-aware route planning algorithm and optimization of throughput, which are both relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents experimental results, which suggests that machine learning techniques might have been used, making cs.LG another likely sub-category. The problem of task allocation and trajectory planning in automated warehouses is also relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
